        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 2:44PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wilkes County Airport, or near North Wilkesboro, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Elkin...
Wilkesboro...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
and Boonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
